---

Summary of every change from your original:

| What changed | Why |
|---|---|
| `MOBILE_BREAKPOINT = 1024` | Hides on half-screen desktop / matches mobile MF breakpoint |
| `isMobile()` evaluated at call-time | Correct value even if script loads before layout settles |
| Removed `_heartbeat` + `startHeartbeat()` entirely | `setInterval` was causing scroll jumps on re-mount |
| Added `_containerObserver` + `startContainerObserver()` | Surgical observer — only fires when container actually mutates |
| DOM insertions wrapped in `requestAnimationFrame` | Defers layout shift to next paint, prevents scroll jump |
| `_resizeTimer` + `onResizeDebounced()` | Prevents layout thrashing while dragging window edge |
| `_containerObserver` disconnected on resize to mobile | Stops watching when widget is removed |
| `_containerObserver` disconnected in destroy | Full cleanup, no memory leaks |
| `window.removeEventListener("resize", onResizeDebounced)` | Must match the exact function reference passed to `addEventListener` |
| `startCarousel()` moved inside `requestAnimationFrame` | Carousel starts only after nodes are actually in DOM |
